owltools.cli

Class CommandRunner

  • java.lang.Object
    • owltools.cli.CommandRunner
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    GafCommandRunner

    public class CommandRunner
extends Object
    An instance of this class can execute owltools commands in sequence. Typically, this class is called from a wrapper within its main() method. Extend this class to implement additional functions. Use the CLIMethod annotation, to designate the relevant methods.
    Author:
    cjm
    See Also:
    GafCommandRunner, JsCommandRunner, SimCommandRunner, SolrCommandRunner, TaxonCommandRunner

      • createPartOfLinks

        public void createPartOfLinks(Opts opts)
                       throws Exception
        GeneOntology specific function to create links between molecular functions and their corresponding processes. This method uses the exact matching of the equivalence axioms to establish the part_of relations.
        All relations created by this method are going to be tagged with an axiom annotation http://purl.org/dc/terms/source and corresponding GO_REF.
        Parameters:
        opts -
        Throws:
        Exception

      • filterExtensionFile

        public void filterExtensionFile(Opts opts)
                         throws Exception
        Retain only subclass of axioms and intersection of axioms if they contain a class in it's signature of a given set of parent terms. For example, to create the x-chemical.owl do the following steps:
        1. Load ChEBI as main ontology graph
        2. (Optional) load go, recommended for OBO write
        3. Setup reasoner: '--elk --init-reasoner'
        4. '--filter-extension-file'
        5. Load extensions file using: '-e' or '--extension-file'
        6. Add required root terms: '-t' or '--term', use multiple paramteres to add multiple terms
        7. Set ontology IRI for filtered file: '-id' or '--ontology-id'
        8. set output files:
          • OWL: '-owl|--output-owl' owl-filename
          • OBO: '-obo|--output-obo' obo-filename
        9. (Optional) set version: '-v' or '--version'
        Parameters:
        opts -
        Throws:
        Exception
